related_questions.question: What is pudding made out of?
related_questions.snippet: pudding, any of several foods whose common characteristic is a relatively soft, spongy, and thick texture. In the United States, puddings are nearly always sweet desserts of milk or fruit juice variously flavoured and thickened with cornstarch, arrowroot, flour, tapioca, rice, bread, or eggs.
related_questions.title: Pudding | Definition, Types, & Ingredients - Britannica

related_questions.question: What is British pudding called in America?
related_questions.snippet: American puddings are closer to what the Brits would call “custard.” A British pudding is a dish, savory or sweet, that's cooked by being boiled or steamed in something: a dish, a piece of cloth, or even animal intestine.
related_questions.title: custard

related_questions.question: Why do British say pudding?
related_questions.snippet: Traditionally, pudding referred to homely and rustic desserts that were commonly eaten by the lower classes, such as spotted dick and rice pudding. Desserts were the indulgences of the upper classes and included international cuisine like chocolate mousse, soufflé and Champagne jelly.
related_questions.title: Why do Brits call dessert pudding? - Great British Mag

related_questions.question: What is Japanese pudding made of?
related_questions.snippet: Purin (プリン) is a custard dessert made from eggs, milk, and sugar, and covered with a thin layer of rich caramel sauce on top. It's basically a Japanese take on crème caramel, also known as flan, custard pudding, or caramel pudding.

answer_box.snippet: In the United States, pudding means a sweet, milk-based dessert similar in consistency to egg-based custards, instant custards or a mousse, often commercially set using cornstarch, gelatin or similar coagulating agent.

buttons.title: What is a pudding? | British Food: A History
buttons.snippet: In America, it is a simple answer: a dessert. We all use pudding to mean dessert or afters, but then there are types of dessert that are true puddings. The true puddings are those that are boiled or steamed. Christmas puddings, suet puddings and sponge puddings fit into this category.
